HEADWORD: Noberts lines
<hw>No"bert's lines</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After <person>F. A.
<etsep>Nobert</etsep></person>, German manufacturer in Pomerania.]</ety>
<def>Fine lines ruled on glass in a series of groups of different
closeness of line, and used to test the power of a microscope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nobiliary</ent>⟦br⟧
